manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: London Fog Newcastle 4 Piece Set You will travel with confidence along with your Newcastle 4 Piece Spinner Luggage Set and feel like you're traveling first class. The London Fog Newcastle Collection gives you a classic yet stylish feel. Made of durable woven herringbone material sure to withstand all your travels. Available in Rose Charcoal Herringbone and Slate Bronze Herringbone. This set is perfect for your short, mid or long length getaways and you will have all the pieces you need. In addition to having plenty of room for all your travel needs, the spinner uprights have 8-low profile spinner wheels and come with a 10 Year Limited Warranty. Depending on your travel needs, you can use all the bags for yourself or share the set with your family. This collection has 3 spinner sizes (20" expandable carry-on spinner, 24" expandable spinner and a 28" expandable spinner) as well as a 17" cabin bag as an added carry-on piece for use during your travels.

Additional Features Piggyback feature design The back of the cabin bag offers a design that will allow you to slide it over your upright handle for easy carrying. If you don't want to use this feature the back will become a pocket for extra organization. There are pockets on both the inside and outside of the bag which help with organization as well. 8 low profile spinner wheels The 20", 24" and 28" Spinners feature 8 low profile spinner wheels that are positioned at the corners for superior balance & smooth rolling along with fitting today's airline standards. Locking Push Button Handle The Spinners have an aluminum locking push button handle system with channels for added strength. Rear Identification pocket on back and the spinners expand 2" for additional packing capacity. Spacious Interior Has full color contrast London Fog Signature lining. The interior has 2 hoe pockets, zippered mesh pocket, zippered accessory pocket and tie down straps to keep your items neatly stored.

reviews.reviewText: Very light. Quality is excellent. Love the wheels. And it’s very good looking.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, Attractive, Lightweight Luggage!
reviews.reviewText: At 59 years of age, I finally purchased my very own full set of matching luggage, and what a great choice I made. Love everything about this set. Lightweight with a handle on the top, bottom and one side of each suitcase, making them so easy to maneuver. Wheeling through the airport was a breeze, and all held up beautifully during their first/only use thus far, on a flight from CA to PA. One of the flight attendants even commented on “what a nice set of luggage” I had. Preferring suitcases with one large compartment rather than two separate sides folding together, I was able to stuff so many belongings into these suitcases while still keeping them manageable at 35-40 lbs. The smallest bag, which easily piggybacks the carry-on, was used as my purse, providing loads more space than a typical purse. All four pieces nest inside one another, requiring much less storage space. What more can I say? Very happy customer! Highly recommend this great set of luggage!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this suitcase!
reviews.reviewText: Had to travel frequently for several months. Bought this suitcase bc it was on sale. It has held up beautifully, looks good, and holds a lot! It’s made well and of good quality. I’m planning to buy additional pieces in the near future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My fourth piece from this collection
reviews.reviewText: I loved the three smaller pieces from this collection but wanted a bigger piece for a longer trip. Same great quality and stylish look! But the spinner wheels were not quite as smooth on this one. Once I got used to it, the wheels were fine. Love the fabric, the features, and the quality!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Amazon ruined Christmas, but
reviews.reviewText: Thank you Amazon for shipping it in the manufacturer's box with "London Fog Luggage" written all over it. You really are considerate of people. smh. It is a beautiful piece of luggage, and WOULD have been a nice surprise. I do have concerns about the lightness of the color, but I think some fabric guard will help. It looks like a nice suitcase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I bought this suitcase to replace one that did not roll well and was always tipping over. I finally got to use this on a vacation - through 2 airports, on 2 planes, in and out of the car. It is great so far. It wheels easily and does not tip over. It is very light weight and seems to have more capacity as another suitcase I have with the same supposed dimensions. Hopefully it will serve me well on future trips.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I love this suitcase. It is really big and roomy, moves really well, and is very lightweight. Just as everyone else has said, it does get fairly dirty when flying. I put scotch guard on it when it first came as others had recommended. After my trip, I was able to clean it fairly quickly and easily, and the dirt came off for the most part, however doesn't look new anymore.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Heavy and filthy
reviews.reviewText: 28" weighs 11.9 pounds when EMPTY - When filled with typical travel items you need a body builder to help lift this thing onto the airport scale and prepare for the "you're 8 pounds overweight" or something similar.After a single plane trip, the Rose colored suitcase is irretrievably filthy - Foolishly, I ordered two of these horrible suitcases while on a trip and because of the incredibly short return window (30 days) I lost my chance to initiate a refund of these horrible bags. Live and learn. I hope this message opens the eyes of at least one unsuspecting buyer.
